## Working this repo

This repo uses the **GitOS agent system** (`~/.claude/skills/gitos/`).

- **Work** (open tasks, work-orders, evidence): `{{HOME}}/INDEX.md` + `{{HOME}}/work-orders/`
- **Memory** (long-term knowledge, decisions, entities): `{{HOME}}/brain/`
- **Roles** (inception / orchestrator / diagnostic / implementer): `{{HOME}}/roles/`
- **Birth certificate**: `{{HOME}}/HANDOFF.md` (read once at session start)

To start a session: invoke the `gitos` skill — it detects the current state and routes
to the correct role automatically.

**Canary — your way back.** Every reply opens with `[gitos · <role> · <focus>]` (role =
orchestrator / diagnostic / implementer / inception; focus = current work-order + step).
**If your last reply had no such marker, your context has drifted** — re-read
`~/.claude/skills/gitos/SKILL.md`, re-detect your role, run
`python {{HOME}}/tools/canary.py {{HOME}}`, and resume marking. This block is a durable
backstop the harness reloads into every window, so it survives even when the skill
directive washes out under compaction; if you can read it, you can recover. It is a
signal, not a guarantee — the operator's glance at the first line is the final check.
